    "whatItDoes": "Terraform Stacks adds a configuration layer above traditional Terraform modules for managing infrastructure across multiple environments, regions, and cloud accounts. It introduces two file types (.tfcomponent.hcl and .tfdeploy.hcl) that define reusable components and deployment instances separately. A single stack can drive dozens of deployments with isolated state per environment.",
